  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Line a 12-cup Madeleine pan with parchment paper.",
    "In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, and salt.",
    "Add the unsalted butter and mix until a crumbly mixture forms.",
    "Beat in the large eggs and vanilla extract until well combined.",
    "Stir in the pine nuts.",
    "Spoon the batter into the prepared Madeleine pan and smooth the tops.",
    "Bake for 12-14 minutes, or until golden brown.",
    "Remove the Madeleine from the oven and let cool in the pan for 5 minutes.",
    "Transfer the Madeleine to a wire rack to cool completely.",
    "Once the Madeleine is cool, dust with granulated sugar and confectioners sugar.",
    "Optional: drizzle with heavy cream for added richness."
  ],
